WITH FilteredData AS (
    SELECT 
        c.Segment,
        y.Consumption
    FROM 
        customers c
    INNER JOIN 
        yearmonth y
    ON 
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE 
        c.Currency = 'CZK' 
        AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
),
LowestConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        Segment,
        MIN(Consumption) AS MinConsumption
    FROM 
        FilteredData
    GROUP BY 
        Segment
),
LowestConsumptionCustomers AS (
    SELECT 
        f.Segment,
        COUNT(*) AS NumLowestConsumptionCustomers
    FROM 
        FilteredData f
    INNER JOIN 
        LowestConsumption l
    ON 
        f.Segment = l.Segment AND f.Consumption = l.MinConsumption
    GROUP BY 
        f.Segment
),
TotalConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        Segment,
        SUM(Consumption) AS TotalConsumption
    FROM 
        FilteredData
    GROUP BY 
        Segment
),
AnnualAverage AS (
    SELECT 
        t.Segment,
        t.TotalConsumption / l.NumLowestConsumptionCustomers AS AnnualAverage
    FROM 
        TotalConsumption t
    INNER JOIN 
        LowestConsumptionCustomers l
    ON 
        t.Segment = l.Segment
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS SME_LAM_Difference,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS LAM_KAM_Difference,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS KAM_SME_Difference;

-- SQL query to determine whether the tallest or shortest player has the highest average finishing rate
WITH PlayerFinishing AS (
    SELECT
        P.player_api_id,
        AVG(PA.finishing) AS avg_finishing
    FROM
        Player P
    INNER JOIN
        Player_Attributes PA
    ON
        P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
    GROUP BY
        P.player_api_id
),
TallestPlayer AS (
    SELECT
        player_api_id
    FROM
        Player
    ORDER BY
        height DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
ShortestPlayer AS (
    SELECT
        player_api_id
    FROM
        Player
    ORDER BY
        height ASC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT
    CASE
        WHEN PF1.avg_finishing > PF2.avg_finishing THEN 'highest'
        ELSE 'shortest'
    END AS result
FROM
    PlayerFinishing PF1
JOIN
    TallestPlayer TP
ON
    PF1.player_api_id = TP.player_api_id
JOIN
    PlayerFinishing PF2
JOIN
    ShortestPlayer SP
ON
    PF2.player_api_id = SP.player_api_id;

        r.name AS race_name,

champion_time AS (

        MIN(CAST(SUBSTR(time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 + 
            CAST(SUBSTR(time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 + 
            CAST(SUBSTR(time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 + 
            CAST(SUBSTR(time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER)) AS champion_milliseconds
    FROM results res
    INNER JOIN race_info ri ON res.raceId = ri.raceId
    WHERE res.time IS NOT NULL
),
last_driver_time AS (
    SELECT 
        MAX(CAST(SUBSTR(time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 + 
            CAST(SUBSTR(time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 + 
            CAST(SUBSTR(time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 + 
            CAST(SUBSTR(time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER)) AS last_driver_milliseconds
    FROM results res
    INNER JOIN race_info ri ON res.raceId = ri.raceId
    WHERE res.time IS NOT NULL
)
SELECT 
    (1 - (champion_time.champion_milliseconds * 1.0 / last_driver_time.last_driver_milliseconds)) * 100 AS percentage_difference
FROM champion_time, last_driver_time;
